article.description: Kelsey Griffin made all nine of her shots and finished with 27 points in just 22 minutes, helping No. 13 Nebraska remained unbeaten with an 88-41 victory over Albany on Wednesday.
article.headline: Nebraska continues best-ever start with easy win
article.linkText: Nebraska remains unbeaten with rout of Albany
article.story:
LINCOLN, Neb. --  Kelsey Griffin made all nine of her shots and finished with 27 points in just 22 minutes, helping  Nebraska (No. 14 ESPN/USA Today; No. 13 AP) remained unbeaten with an 88-41 victory over Albany on Wednesday.

Griffin hit two 3-poiners and was 7 for 7 from the free throw line as the Cornhuskers (12-0) extended their school-record winning streak and best start to a season.

Cory Montgomery added 14 points, Dominique Kelley 12 and Catheryn Redmon 10 for Nebraska.

Lincoln native Charity Iromuanya had 10 points for Albany (6-5).

Nebraska led 53-24 at halftime before a 22-0 run put the Huskers up 79-28 with 6:36 left.

The Huskers are one of seven unbeaten teams left in Division I, and the only one in the Big 12.
